# Override-Layer Precedence

When design knowledge is spread across many documents that were written at different times, contradictions are inevitable. Resolve them deterministically with a **single override layer** instead of editing every doc.

## The rule
- **`{{OVERRIDE_DOC_PATH}}` overrides contradictions in all other design docs.** When any other doc and the override doc conflict, the override doc wins.
- The override doc is produced *after* a full review (e.g. a pre-build Q&A pass). It carries confirmed field-name corrections, platform-constraint resolutions, and locked decisions.
- Items flagged **⚠️ OVERRIDES SPEC** mean the original doc is wrong — use the override value.
- **Do not back-edit** the superseded docs to "fix" them. Treat the override doc as a layer, not a patch — this preserves the audit trail of what changed and why.

## Reading order
Always read in this order before writing code:
1. `{{ORIENTATION_DOC}}` (e.g. `AGENTS.md` / `AGENT_REFERENCE.md`) — goals, constraints, data model.
2. `{{OVERRIDE_DOC_PATH}}` — the override layer. Read second.
3. The remaining design-doc sections in their numbered order.

